OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 26 Jul to Tue 4 AugFA
OL,6,Fchangeable period is likely overall,
OL,7,Fwith many areas likely to see a
OL,8,Fmixture of bright or sunny spells and
OL,9,Fsome rain at times. Northwestern areas
OL,10,Fare more likely to see the focus of
OL,11,Frainfall, but southeastern areas
OL,12,Fshould also see some showers.
OL,13,FConfidence becomes lower as we
OL,14,Fapproach the turn of the month, but
OL,15,Fthere are hints that high pressure
OL,16,Fcould return for a time, which would
OL,17,Fmean dry conditions resuming,
OL,18,Fespecially in the south. Winds will be
OL,19,Fmostly light or moderate, but
OL,20,Foccasionally fresh or strong around
OL,21,Fsome coasts, mainly in the north.
OL,22,FTemperatures will be near or above
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fnormal, warmest in the south, and
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fperhaps becoming very warm again by
OL,25,Fthe start of August.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
